x4freetext: -INELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS OF NEUTRONS OF
I-127(SOLID) RESPECTIVELY.SB AND AG WERE NATURAL.
PROTON RECOIL PROPORTIONAL COUNTER,6CM IN DIAM,
26CM IN LENGTH,FILLED WITH 2ATM. HIGH PURITY CH4,AND
0.5 PC HE-3 ADMIXTURE FOR ENERGY CALIBRATION.
.NEUTRON SPECTRA WERE DEDUCED ACCORDING TO THE METHOD
TO H.A.BETHE ET AL.,JOURNAL OF NUCL.ENERGY,3,(1956),
TO THE METHOD OF N.L.SNIDOW AND H.D.WARREN,NUCLEAR
.MULTIPLE SCATTERING CORRECTION IN THE SCATTERER BY
MONTE-CARLO METHOD,SEE K.MUECK ET AL.,J.OF N.ENERGY,
MULTIPLE SCATTERING IN THE THICK SCATTERER,SCATTERER
.AVERAGE EXCITATION ENERGY ERROR FOR FINAL NUCLEUS,
WAS DEDUCED FROM INELASTIC SCATTERED NEUTRON SPECTRA.
